Static Members

Static members belong to the class itself, not to instances.

### Static Properties

```typescript
class MathUtils {
  static PI: number = 3.14159;
  static E: number = 2.71828;
}

console.log(MathUtils.PI); // 3.14159
// Access via class, not instance
```

### Static Methods

```typescript
class StringUtils {
  static capitalize(str: string): string {
    return str.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + str.slice(1);
  }

  static isNullOrEmpty(str: string | null | undefined): boolean {
    return str === null || str === undefined || str === "";
  }
}

console.log(StringUtils.capitalize("hello")); // "Hello"
```

### Static Members in Inheritance

```typescript
class Base {
  static id: number = 1;
  static getClassName(): string {
    return "Base";
  }
}

class Derived extends Base {
  static getClassName(): string {
    return "Derived";
  }
}

console.log(Derived.id); // 1 (inherited)
console.log(Derived.getClassName()); // "Derived"
```

### Static vs Instance

| Feature | Static | Instance |
|---------|--------|----------|
| Access | ClassName.member | instance.member |
| Belongs to | Class | Instance |
| Access to instance members | No | Yes |
| Access to static members | Yes | Yes |
| Memory | One copy shared | One per instance |

### Static Blocks

TypeScript supports static initialization blocks:

```typescript
class Database {
  static connection: string;

  static {
    // Static initialization block
    this.connection = "connected";
    console.log("Database initialized");
  }
}
```

> **Key Point:** Static methods cannot access `this` for instance members — they have no instance context.

codeExample:
class Counter {
  private static count: number = 0;

  static increment(): number {
    return ++Counter.count;
  }

  static getCount(): number {
    return Counter.count;
  }

  static reset(): void {
    Counter.count = 0;
  }
}

console.log(Counter.increment()); // 1
console.log(Counter.increment()); // 2
console.log(Counter.getCount()); // 2
Counter.reset();
console.log(Counter.getCount()); // 0

// Utility class with static members
class URLBuilder {
  static create(base: string, path: string): string {
    return `${base.replace(/\/+$/, "")}/${path.replace(/^\/+/, "")}`;
  }
}
